Synopsis:
   setpassword <user> [nocrypt] <password>

Description:
   This command sets new password for user in userlist.  This is useful
   if the user has forgotten his password and asks you to change it.

   If the second argument is "nocrypt", the password will be saved
   non-crypted.  This is used internally by userlist.

See Also:
   delpassword(9); userlist(9)

